The paper proposes a neural framework for learning constraint satisfaction solvers, which involves the use of Graph Neural Networks and probabilistic inference. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Computation and Language (cs.CL), and Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV). Among these, cs.AI and cs.LG are the most likely categories, as they are directly related to the use of neural networks for solving constraint satisfaction problems. The other categories are also possible, as they involve topics such as optimization, probabilistic inference, and graphical models, which are relevant to the proposed framework.
